T1  - A social accounting matrix for Egypt, 1976
AU  - Eckaus, Richard S.
AU  - McCarthy, F.Desmond
AU  - Mohie-Eldin, Amr
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 9
IS  - 2
SP  - 183
EP  - 203
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/10/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(81)90036-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387881900365
AB  - A 1976 Social Accounting Matrix for Egypt is presented and the methods of estimation used are described briefly. Some of the implications of the accounting are discussed. The information on the distribution of taxes and subsidies indicates that the latter are the major source of progressiveness in the fiscal system. In relation to their incomes, rural households are also shown to pay less in taxes and receive less in subsidies than urban households.
